text: Nathan Nelson is an American politician and a Republican member of the Minnesota House of Representatives. He represents District 11B in east-central Minnesota. ==Early life, education, and career== Nelson was born in Hinckley, Minnesota and graduated from Hinckley-Finlayson High School in 1997. He was a member of the Clover Township board of supervisors for nine years and is the president of the Pine County Farm Bureau. ==Minnesota House of Representatives== Nelson was first elected to the Minnesota House of Representatives in a special election in 2019. ==Personal life== Nelson and his wife, Suzanna, have five children.
